                            <comment id="16307049" author="paulk" created="Sun, 31 Dec 2017 03:05:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks for your PRs! WRT master being already fixed, I noticed that if I set -Dgroovy.antlr4=false in master I get the same error and on 2.6 if I set that flag to true I don&apos;t get the error but otherwise all looks good. Don&apos;t create another PR though - it&apos;s just as easy (and better for tracking) for me to cherry-pick the change in master onto the other branches where the source files are in the same directory, i.e. all except 2_4_X. The only thing I wanted to check was coverage. One of the historic commits in the area of this change talks about a whole block being classed as covered if only one line was executed - so I just want to check that doesn&apos;t happen here before applying.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
